# CLI Rules

For command-line interface code:

1. Use System.CommandLine for argument parsing
2. Provide helpful error messages and usage examples
3. Support both interactive and command modes
4. Follow POSIX command-line conventions
5. Include command help documentation
6. Handle CTRL+C gracefully
7. Support verbose/quiet output modes 